**üßê Motivation**
ERC721Consecutive : next id is pain in this scenario. why not use something like snippet in below:
```solidity
function consecutiveTransfer(
        uint256 fromTokenId,
        uint256 toTokenId,
        address fromAddress,
        address toAddress
    ) public {
        require(fromTokenId <= toTokenId, "Invalid token range");

        _consecutiveTransfer(fromTokenId, toTokenId, fromAddress, toAddress);
    }

    function _consecutiveTransfer(
        uint256 currentTokenId,
        uint256 toTokenId,
        address fromAddress,
        address toAddress
    ) private {
        emit ConsecutiveTransfer(currentTokenId, currentTokenId, fromAddress, toAddress);

        if (currentTokenId < toTokenId) {
            _consecutiveTransfer(currentTokenId + 1, toTokenId, fromAddress, toAddress);
        }
    }
```
**openzeppelin v5 make Althing's better to use, but some codes make pain! 
thanks for response from community**

**üìù Details**
[ERC721Consecutive](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/7de6fd4a2604764497990bcc0013f95763713190/contracts/token/ERC721/extensions/ERC721Consecutive.sol#L104) - [next id](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/7de6fd4a2604764497990bcc0013f95763713190/contracts/token/ERC721/extensions/ERC721Consecutive.sol#L172)

